    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for adding `next/geo`:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 files total** — 4 new, 1 modified. All patterns cloned directly from the `userAgent` / `server.js` approach.\n\n### Files\n\n| Action | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| Create | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| Create | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| Create | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| Modify | `packages/next/package.json` |\n| Create | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `geo.ts` (core implementation)\n\nMirrors `user-agent.ts` exactly — no external imports, pure TypeScript:\n\n- **`Geo` interface**: 7 optional string fields (`city`, `country`, `countryCode`, `region`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `timezone`)\n- **`COUNTRY_NAMES`** map: 10 entries (US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n- **`geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo`**: reads `x-vercel-ip-*` headers; falls back to `cf-ipcountry` for `countryCode`; derives `country` from map; converts `null` → `undefined` via `?? undefined`\n- **`geo({ headers }): Geo`**: thin wrapper calling `geoFromHeaders` (mirrors `userAgent()` → `userAgentFromString()`)\n- **`isInRegion(geo, regions): boolean`**: case-insensitive `countryCode` match\n- **`geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2): number`**: Haversine formula, returns km\n\n### Step 2 — `geo.js` (CJS entry point)\n\nExact copy of `server.js` pattern: build `geoExports` object with `require('next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo').xxx`, set `module.exports = geoExports`, then assign each named export to `exports.xxx` for ESM interop.\n\n### Step 3 — `geo.d.ts` (type definitions)\n\nRe-exports everything from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`, mirroring `server.d.ts`.\n\n### Step 4 — `package.json` edit\n\nInsert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` into the `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetically `g` follows `f`).\n\n### Step 5 — `geo.test.ts` (Jest tests)\n\n9 test cases using Jest's `describe/it/expect` (same as `adapters/headers.test.ts` nearby):\n- `geo()` with full Vercel headers — all 7 fields populated\n- `geo()` with no headers — all fields `undefined`\n- `geoFromHeaders()` with only `cf-ipcountry` — fallback works\n- `geoFromHeaders()` with both headers — Vercel takes precedence\n- `geoFromHeaders()` with unknown countryCode — `country` is `undefined`\n- `isInRegion()` match (case-insensitive)\n- `isInRegion()` no match\n- `isInRegion()` with `countryCode: undefined`\n- `geoDistance()` NY→London (expect 5520–5620 km)\n- `geoDistance()` identical points (expect ≈0)\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types          # TypeScript check (~10s)\npnpm --filter=next build          # Compile to dist/\npnpm test-unit packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts\n```",
